<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                            <head>No. 585.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName type="to">Sickles</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-07"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 7,
                                        1873</date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The capture on the high seas of a vessel bearing the American flag
                                presents a very grave question, which will need investigation, and
                                the summary proceedings resulting in the punishment of death, with
                                such rapid haste, will attract attention as inhuman and in violation
                                of the civilization of the age. And if it prove that an American
                                citizen has been wrongfully executed, this Government will require
                                most ample reparation.</p>
                            <closer><signed>FISH,</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>